HEADWORD: Chitin
<hw>Chi"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Chiton</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white amorphous horny
substance forming the harder part of the outer integument of insects,
crustacea, and various other invertebrates; entomolin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

